      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to all governing equations (continuity, momentum, species transport for hemolysis scalar). Observed order of accuracy confirmed within 2% of theoretical order for all spatial and temporal discretization schemes. Code verification report independently audited."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Three-level Richardson extrapolation performed on systematically refined meshes (3.2M, 12.8M, 51.2M cells; refinement ratio 2). Grid convergence index (GCI) computed per ASME V&V 20. GCI_fine < 1.2% for hemolysis index QoI at all 5 operating points. Temporal convergence confirmed via three time-step refinements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) documented with calibrated instrumentation traceable to NIST standards. Uncertainty in boundary conditions propagated through Monte Carlo ensemble. All 5 COU operating points replicated in experimental test matrix with ≤0.5% deviation in set-point conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Quantitative validation metric: normalized root-mean-square error (NRMSE) for hemolysis index ≤ 8% across all 5 operating points. Validation comparison includes experimental measurement uncertainty (95% CI) and model prediction interval from Monte Carlo UQ. Validation dashboard linked to https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-absolute-5op."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is the direct clinical surrogate for red blood cell damage used in FDA guidance. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) are mechanistically linked to NIH through validated power-law hemolysis model. Clinical threshold mapping confirmed with hematologist review panel."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments performed on the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under the same 5 COU operating points (flow rates 2.5–7 L/min, speeds 2500–3500 RPM). Fluid: bovine blood at physiologic hematocrit. No geometric or operating extrapolation required. Validation domain fully envelops COU domain per ASME V&V 40 §6.4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence verified: all residuals below 1×10⁻⁷ for continuity and momentum, 1×10⁻⁹ for hemolysis scalar. Round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic audit. Solver error contribution to total numerical uncertainty estimated at <0.3% via ASME V&V 20 decomposition, negligible relative to discretization error."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Simulation execution governed by controlled simulation protocol document (SPD-VAD-002 rev C). Independent replication by second analyst confirmed identical results within floating-point reproducibility. Automated pre/post-processing scripts version-controlled and peer-reviewed. User qualification records on file for all analysts."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Turbulence model (SST k-ω) selected after systematic comparison of five candidate models (k-ε, k-ω, SST k-ω, RSM, LES) against PIV benchmark data. SST k-ω achieved lowest velocity field NRMSE (4.1%). Hemolysis power-law exponents (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) recalibrated against in-vitro shear device data. Model form uncertainty quantified via model-form error term in validation metric."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5",
      "rationale": "All 12 uncertain input parameters (viscosity, density, hematocrit, hemolysis model coefficients, turbulence intensity, wall roughness, rotational speed uncertainty, flow rate uncertainty, and 4 geometric tolerances) characterized with probability distributions from experimental measurement campaigns. Global Sobol sensitivity analysis (10,000 quasi-random samples) identifies hemolysis model exponent α as dominant input (S_T = 0.61). Full input uncertainty propagation via Monte Carlo linked to https://uofa.net/synth/uq/monte-carlo-hemolysis-10000-runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Experimental dataset comprises n=6 independent test runs per operating point (30 total runs) using fresh bovine blood from qualified donors with hematocrit 35±2%. Sample preparation protocol per ASTM F1841. Inter-run variability characterized; coefficient of variation for NIH ≤ 4.8% across all operating points. Sample size justified by power analysis (β=0.80, α=0.05) for detection of 10% hemolysis difference."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/input-equivalency-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions applied in simulation derived directly from experimental measurements at pump inlet/outlet planes (not assumed values). Fluid rheology parameters measured from each blood batch and input to simulation. Geometric model created from CMM-verified pump dimensions with documented tolerances. Equivalency matrix (simulation input vs. experimental condition) completed for all 12 uncertain parameters; no extrapolation identified."
    }
